snippet.textDisplay: MWP, is obviously holding back as much as he can, and Kobe & Gianna's death, is heartbreaking for him, as it is for many of us. I hope he continues to be strong. For years, he's looked up to Kobe, and he was ecstatic to be his teammate, when they won the title. He has always thanked kobe for his input in becoming a Laker, and helping him reach his goal as becoming an NBA champion. MWP was a beast in that game 7, that decided the title. The Lakers were down by as many as 15 points...Kobe didn't have his best shooting game, but he did have like 15 rebounds and close to 10 assists. MWP hit several big 3's and played great defense on Paul Pierce. He definitely had the "Mamba Mentality" that night. He's come a long way...Keep on pushing brother...
